data.output: The prince swept his fingers dramatically across the keyboard, enjoying the sounds of the organ reverberating around the empty church. He turned around to face the empty pews and barely contained his urge to start throwing the bouquets around the empty space. He didn't feel the need to comply with social norms right now, but still had to maintain a public face if he were to inherit his father's empire. So much for the princess though, she had decided it was all too quick a romance and she 'needed time to think', whatever that meant. And what was he to do in the meantime, just sit and wait?

The sound of the mouth organ played by the beggar on the street was delightful.  He had a good position, just outside the Empire cinema which had been closed for years.   I had heard that the Fire Brigade had it closed down as it did not comply with fire regulations

In an empire someone heard music. They followed the sound and it lead them to someone else playing music on an organ instrument. The person playing the organ was having lessons from a music teacher and did comply with what they were told to play on the instrument. The music was beautiful. The musician was very talented.

The empire was growing stronger, their fierce leader implementing new rules to his citizens daily and ensuring he had eyes all over the place to ensure they comply with the new rules.  He wanted to run a nation that was disciplined and listened to orders.  He was an incredibly extravagant leader, his bedroom almost laughable with how over the top it is.  A large organ in what is now his living area, an organ that he insisted on keeping from the old converted church.

Donation is mandatory for the empire to survive. Some will not comply, but forcible removal of an organ is traumatic and often leads to severe mental illness. The notes hung in the air, almost alive as they echoed around the cathedral. The beauty of an organ when played by a master is an unparalleled delight. I did not know the name of the piece, it was grand and almost military, perhaps a tribute to an empire long since lost to time. It certainly didn't comply with the playlist set for Michaelmas term this year, as I knew all those compositions by heart.

In 2142, the British empire has a problem. With the lack of jobs many have turned to organ sharks. If you take a loan from them and don't pay them back they give you a warning. After some time has passed, and you still don't comply, they come and gut you for what you have usually taking a liver or kidney. Gutted people are called husks which are marked by the organ sharks.

My favourire bodily organ is my right eye. With it, I can see the whole vista of the empire when I stand at the highest point of the island. The laws of optics suggest it shouldn't be so, but in magic worlds eyes don't have to comply with the laws of terrestial physics

My friend Archie is gravely ill and needs a new organ as hHis Kidney is failing rapidly and in need of a transplant. The NHS empire, our National Health Service says I am a matching donor, I have a problem in as much as I love my friend very much, but I am not 100% sure I want to comply and go ahead with giving up one of my kidneys, even for my dear friend. I am worried about my future health needs.

I was privalidged to attend a big show last week. There was a man playing the organ. Apparently he started with one and then bought a store . He started his own company and now has grown to a milion pound empire. As it was so entertaining i found it hard to comply with the rules and not start singing and clapping.

'Good morning Emma! Are you here to donate your kidney today? You're so very kind! Organ donation is such a generous thing to do.' 'Yes, Rhi promised me some new books on the Empire of Glass if I went for it! So here I am ready to comply. I'll do anything for a good book!' Emma beamed in excitement.

There is a belief that the most beautiful instrument is the organ, which you might find gracing a church and whose music might sound melodic to your ears. To me, this instrument makes me think of centuries of kings and queens who forced people to comply. The empire that they built based on the expectation that the people needed them. So I prefer the lute.

It's so hard for me to comply with the rules at school. All I wanted to play that day was Empire Earth on my phone, and I wasn't even doing it in class. It was at lunchtime. But my biology teacher caught me and sent me to her classroom to wait for her. While I waited, I looked at the poster on her wall depicting the organ system of the body.

The organ was terribly loud. The organist was pumping away like fury, playing music written to celebrate the Empire; practicing his vigourous harmonies to perfection. It was a wonder to hear it. I was thrilled to bits to see the extent to which he wet in order to comply with my wishes for the upcoming celebrations. The Empire has not been forgotten and we will proudly march into the hall to this, the most stirring of music.

I tried very hard to play the organ, I wanted to so badly. I hated the man who stood on top of his empire of tunes. I wanted to have my own library of hymns to move the masses. I needed to have 5 years experience in the church before I could make this a reality. I must comply with these rules, and then I could be the organ master I always wanted to become.

"I dream of having my own cleaning empire someday" Sohail smiled at the panel. He was attending an interview for an internship at Organ NIZE - a professional organising company who visit clients and organise and clean their home, office, or other space for them. "My strengths involve complying with all policies and procedures, following safety regulations, and putting the clients needs first".

I am very good at playing the organ such that I was invited to play at a ceremony for the giving of medals. When it came to the empire medal I had to play specific music to comply with the requirements of the ceremony

Our local church had received a letter from the council to let them know that the organ that is played regularly at the church services needed to comply with regulation for health and safety reasons.  The minister asked me if I knew anyone who could possibly help with this as he didn't know the first thing about it!! I asked my friend who worked at the Empire theatre in the town if she knew anyone who perhaps would be able to do it.  Luckily we found someone!!!  Thank goodness!!!

Daisy also wanted to be a  transplant surgeon. The thought of holding an organ in her hand and having to comply with the regulations of the GMC board everyday excited her. However, due to the financial demands of medical school, Daisy had to open a lash business, which seemed to be taking up more time then she has ever proposed. During her last year Daisy decided to close her well known business empire down and focus on studying to become the surgeon she always wanted to be.

Daisy wondered what it would be like to receive someone else's organ. She wondered if she would gain any special powers from the other person. "Imagine if the donor had ruled an empire!" she exclaimed. "Will I be more powerful?!" But Daisy also knew that to receive the organ she would need to comply with the doctors.

The Empire Theatre was a classic. It was fitted with beautiful, original Art Deco features and an organ set by the stage. It wouldn't comply with any of today's building regulations but I don't think anyone would want to change it.

the surgery was difficult and long. The patient's organ had failed at the last minute. It was a heart failure, and the surgeon is not positive she did her best, although every step in the operation was strictly followed and she had to comply with the patient's needs. In this day and age, we don't expect to fail during surgery, an entire empire of lawyers is waiting outside of the operating room to hear of your failure. still, there is hope she could explain all to the family and the other doctors support her decision.

He would not listen, Intransigent in his beliefs that the country is which he lived was justified in his imperial conquest of the world. An empire of beliefs. An empire where the sun never set. He did not understand the absurdity of his supremacism, and in his own limited mind believe that there was nothing wrong in bending the will of others he saw as beneath him - comply or be repressed. Comply or be subdued. Like a festering organ, he disgorged his retrograde beliefs and I wondered if I ever really knew him at all. Was this what others thought? Believed. That some men were meant to rule others by virtue of some unknown inherent sense of superiority?  The friendship would be forever broken. I was certain of this.
